HEADWORD: Rhamnus
<hw>Rham"nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<grk>"ra`mnos</grk> a kind of prickly shrub; cf. L.
<ets>rhamnos</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of shrubs and
small trees; buckthorn. The California <spn>Rhamnus Purshianus</spn> and
the European <spn>Rhamnus catharticus</spn> are used in medicine. The
latter is used for hedges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhamphorhynchus</ent>⟦br⟧
